data.chText: 找不到的；不在的；丢失的
data.enText: that cannot be found or that is not in its usual place, or at home

data.chText: 我一直没找到丢了的那件。
data.enText: I never found the missing piece.

data.chText: 我的手套已经丢了很久了。
data.enText: My gloves have been missing for ages.

data.chText: 他们仍然希望找到他们丢失的儿子。
data.enText: They still hoped to find their missing son.

data.chText: 被去除的；丢失的；被损毁的；缺少的
data.enText: that has been removed, lost or destroyed and has not been replaced
The book has two pages missing/missing pages.

data.chText: 后来他才注意到他的屋里丢了东西。
data.enText: He didn't notice there was anything missing from his room until later on.
not present after an accident, battle, etc. but not known to have been killed

data.chText: 有报道说他失踪了，并推定已经丧生。
data.enText: He was reported missing, presumed dead .

data.chText: 许多士兵都被列在战斗失踪人员名单上。
data.enText: Many soldiers were listed as missing in action .

data.chText: 缺少的；未被包括在内的
data.enText: not included, often when it should have been
Fill in the missing words in this text.

data.chText: 有几名候选人没有出现在名单中。
data.enText: There were several candidates missing from the list.

ex.zh: 仍然丢失（或缺失、漏掉、失踪）的
不见（或缺失、漏掉）的一块

value.def: If something is missing, it is not in its usual place, and you cannot find it.

example.ex: It was only an hour or so later that I discovered that my gun was missing...
example.tran: 仅仅约一个小时之后，我发现我的枪不见了。

example.ex: The playing cards had gone missing.

value.def: If a part of something is missing, it has been removed or has come off, and has not been replaced.

example.ex: Three buttons were missing from his shirt.

value.tran: 被去除的；缺损的；缺掉的

value.def: If you say that something is missing, you mean that it has not been included, and you think that it should have been.

example.ex: What is missing, however, is an internal, artistic cohesion...
example.tran: 不过，缺乏的是一种内在的艺术凝聚力。

example.ex: She had given me an incomplete list. One name was missing from it.
example.tran: 她给我的名单并不完整，有一个名字漏掉了。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>from</l> n

value.def: Someone who is missing cannot be found, and it is not known whether they are alive or dead.

example.ex: Five people died in the explosion and more than one thousand were injured. One person is still missing.
example.tran: 爆炸中有5人死亡，1,000多人受伤，1人至今下落不明。

defx.def: If a member of the armed forces is missing in action, they have not returned from a battle, their body has not been found, and they are not thought to have been captured.
defx.tran: (参战士兵)下落不明，在战斗中失踪

trans: 丢失物质；丢失质量；无踪质量；质量；短缺质量
(理解问题或使事物完整的)必要的环节，不可缺少的一环；缺环(推想中从类人猿发展到人类之间的过渡动物)
失踪；现在书不见了；不见了
